    %section
        %h2.s4 Maximizing timelines & collaboration with an agile workflow
        %p.no-image At each phase of the project, design, copy, and engineering collaborated and worked in parallel. Design would hand off pages to engineering in the wireframe stage and then would go back to add refinement with the comps. This created a quick, iterative process that allowed all teams to maximize timelines.

    %section
        %h2.s4 Creating an effective design system
        %p One of the site redesign challenges was creating an effective design system using Serta’s existing brand colors. The blues and yellows were overutilized and mostly not accessible on white. This made finding a noticeable call-to-action (CTA) color challenging. This effect was compounded by the fact that the Serta team had developed an art direction strategy that relied heavily on blue. So our team set out to find a CTA color that would work well with the existing palette and draw users’ eyes toward making a purchase. We settled on a bright terracotta color to complement the existing blues and yellows while standing out nicely on the page. 
